-- Japan, U.S. Said to Plan Military Drill Amid Regional Tension, Nikkei Says
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2010-12-01T19:50:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/japan-u-s-said-to-plan-military-drill-amid-regional-tension-nikkei-says.html
Japan and the U.S. are planning a
large military exercise, Nikkei English News reported, without
saying how it got the information.  The drill will involve about 34,100 personnel from Japan
and 10,400 U.S. troops, Nikkei said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
